description:
&lt;p&gt;The Priory Hospital Church Village is a 12 bed locked rehabilitation service, providing treatment for females aged 18-65 years with a learning disability and additional mental health diagnosis including personality disorders. Most of our patients are detained under the Mental Health Act.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has come up for you to join our friendly multidisciplinary team of staff including Consultant Psychiatrist, Occupational Therapist, Assistant Psychologist,Mental Health and learning Disability Nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Undertaking specialist structured, semi-structured and standardised psychological assessments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Developing specialist psychological formulations based on assessments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Formulating plans for patients’ psychological treatment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Implementing specialist psychological interventions for individuals and groups&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Working autonomously within professional guidelines and the overall framework of the Hospital’s policies and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Providing support to staff in the form of reflective practice groups, and staff training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Is registered with the HCPC as a practitioner psychologist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Has some experience of working with learning disabilities or behaviours that challenge, or a real desire to develop in this area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Has training in clinical and psychological psychometrics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Is able to use Dialectical Behavioral techniques (DBT), of be willing to undertake further training in this approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Has had training in the use of Positive Behavioral Support (PBS), or be willing to undertake further training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Has skills in individual and group work and in programme planning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Has skills in the use of complex methods of psychological assessment to inform the psychological formulation and intervention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Has well developed skills in the ability to communicate effectively, verbally and in writing, complex, highly technical and / or clinically sensitive information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Has some experience of representing psychology within the context of multi-disciplinary care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we can offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• The opportunity to work with a friendly, dedicated team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• A competitive salary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Enhanced disclosure cost coverage&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Comprehensive induction and commitment to ongoing training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 25 days annual leave plus bank holidays, increasing with length if service.( pro rated)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Birthday off as leave&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Online benefits and cashback rewards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Cycle to work scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• SMART Pension options&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Monthly staff wellbeing initiative&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
